Nine players and a coach were ejected from the stadium after a mass brawl broke out during a minor league baseball game, delaying the game by 15 minutes.

Players clashed on the pitch after running off their benches in a Triple-A game between the Albuquerque Isotopes and the Reno Aces in Reno, Nevada.

The riot erupted when Reno batter Erisbel Arruebarrena reacted furiously after claiming that Aces pitcher Mike Bolsinger had thrown the ball at his body.

