After striking out, Arruebarrena shoved Reno cather Blake Lalli, prompting players from both teams to pour onto the field.

Arruebarrena threw his helmet at one player, who responded by tackling him to the ground with the help of two colleagues.

Around 20 players then started throwing bats, helmets and punches as they wrestled behind the backstop, with some being pushed into netting which separates the spectators.

Aces manager Phil Nevin, who was one of those ejected, insisted he had simply been trying to break up the melee before it spiralled out of control.

