He told Milb.com: 'I think that's kind of my job, to break things up. I'm too old for that stuff.

'It was pretty tough for me to get guys away when guys are throwing bats and helmets at people.'Â 

When the two sides finally separated, the umpires handed out ten ejections.

They included Arruebarrena, Lalli, pitchers Andrew Chafin and Kameron Loe, left fielder Aaron Cunningham and first baseman Mike Jacobs.

Ejected: Nine players and a coach were thrown out of the stadium after the players finally separated

Walter Ibarra and pitchers Carlos Frias and Yimi Garcia from Albuquerque were also thrown out.

Mr Nevin said: 'I understand they (the umpires) have got a job to do. I just took exception to my catcher being thrown out.

'We lost three guys from our line-up and I didn't have that many guys out there to begin with.'

Despite that, the Aces went on to win 7-3 over the visitors.

